AGI - There are many faithful sitting on the benches around the statue of John Paul II on the square of the polyclinic twins in prayer for Pope Francis, admitted for 14 days. For some of them it is also an opportunity to immortalize this moment, so families and boys take advantage of it to take pictures and selfies under the statue of the Polish saint.
&nbsp;
There is also a group of students who are here taking pictures for different reasons: "We just finished all the graduation exams - they explain to AGI - so after six years we can finally look in the eyes this statue".
&nbsp;
There is in fact a tradition, common to many universities, so it brings bad luck to look at the faculty statue before graduating. "Now, after six years, we can finally do it and take advantage of it also to take a photo - they explain - of course it is also the opportunity to send a thought to Pope Francis to whom we love and hope that he will heal soon ", conclude.&nbsp;

